Encode-Deep

The Encode module is used to convert strings between different encodings but
it can't work on references.

Encode::Deep provides the most common Encode functions with reference ability.

Any value is converted using the Encode functions and references are copied and
inspected for additional values.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

	perl Makefile.PL
	make
	make test
	make install

SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the
perldoc command.

    perldoc Encode::Deep

You can also look for information at:

    RT, CPAN's request tracker (report bugs here)
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=Encode-Deep

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/Encode-Deep/

